      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earlville%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Facing the opera house, the Odd Fellows Hall on East Main Street showcases a classic Second Empire mansard roof.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.livingplaces.com/NY/Madison_County/Earlville_Village/Earlville_Historic_District.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The Earlville Opera House, listed in 1973, hosts a theater, two art galleries, a café, and an artisan shop.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
